New Records: Ireland set a new best for their highest opening partnership against South Africa in ODI cricket with a 101-run stand between Paul Stirling and Andrew Balbirnie.
Key Match Events: Harry Tector scored a rapid 60 from 48 balls.
Mark Adair and Graham Hume picked up early wickets to leave South Africa at 8-2.
Adair trapped Rassie van der Dussen lbw to make it 10-3.
Fionn Hand earned his first wicket on his ODI debut by dismissing Andile Phehlukwayo.
Jason Smith scored 91 for South Africa.
Graham Hume picked up the final wicket in the 47th over to secure Ireland's victory.
Pre-Game Insights: Paul Stirling won the toss for the first time in five attempts and elected to bat.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ireland won the match by 69 runs with 23 balls to spare.
The match was held at Zayed Cricket Stadium, Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates.
